questions.prompt:
What does this transaction accomplish and why is error checking important?
```sql
BEGIN TRANSACTION;
UPDATE Accounts SET Balance = Balance - 100 WHERE AccountID = 1;
UPDATE Accounts SET Balance = Balance + 100 WHERE AccountID = 2;
IF @@ERROR <> 0
ROLLBACK TRANSACTION;
ELSE
COMMIT TRANSACTION;
```

